Aran Valley

In 1944, when the Axis powers were about to fall, some spanish communist exiles formerly part of the french Resistance, were sent to the Pyrenees to cross the spanish - french border and stablish a bridgehead for a possible Allied disembark in Spain, thus, taking down the Franco's government. The operation, supported by the spanish Communist Party ended in a complete failure, can you turn the tide?.

Autor: Santiago Fuertes   

Konversion in OG: M. Kessler
